\DOC is_vartype

\TYPE {is_vartype : type -> bool}

\SYNOPSIS
Tests a type to see if it is a type variable, including type operators.

\FAILURE
Never fails.

\EXAMPLE
{
- is_vartype Type.alpha;
> val it = true : bool

- is_vartype bool;
> val it = false : bool

- is_vartype (Type `:'a  -> bool`);
> val it = false : bool
}


\SEEALSO
Type.mk_vartype, Type.mk_vartype_opr, Type.dest_vartype, Type.dest_vartype_opr.
\ENDDOC
